We welcome contributions from the AI and security community! Join our [Discord community](https://discord.gg/QZQpef5PsD) or [Slack community](https://join.slack.com/t/splxaicommunity/shared_invite/zt-31b3hc3mt-A0v78qztTIMSNBg6y~WOAA) to connect with other developers, discuss features, get support and contribute to **Agentic Radar** üöÄ

If you like what you see, give us a star! It keeps us inspired to improve and innovate and helps others discover the project üåü

## Frequently Asked Questions ‚ùì

**Q: Is my source code being shared or is everything running locally?**  
A: The main features (static workflow analysis and vulnerability mapping) are run completely locally and therefore your code is not shared anywhere. For optional advanced features, LLM's might be used. Eg. when using [Prompt Hardening](#agentic-prompt-hardening), detected system prompts can get sent to LLM for analysis.

